stylometry: Fixed cost models are singleing out the fixed cost of a product to see how much of each product to produce to maximize the profit.  You may have 3 different products and considering the cost of each your optimum choice may be to produce only 2 of the 3 to maximize the profit.  Set covering model on the other hand is used in the same content at fixed cost models the only differnce is you are covering less items or controling a smaller area of the problem.  We are trying to see how many of each product, or what ever the problem is, to produce to maximize the profit of your company.
